			<h3>Headache</h3>
			<p>
				A mild, occasional headache is generally not of medical concern.  However, regular and chronic headaches are of serious concern and may be oral and dental related.  Headaches may be directly or indirectly caused or exacerbated by the following dental conditions:
			</p>
			<%= image_tag 'wisdomtooth.jpg', :class => "float-right" %>	
			<ul>
				<li>Toothaches</li>
				<li>Abscesses</li>
				<li>Cavities</li>
				<li>Periodontal disease (Gingivitis and Periodontitis)</li>
				<li>Preeclampsia caused by periodontal disease</li>
				<li>Teething</li>
				<li>Impacted wisdom teeth</li>
				<li>Cold sores and the HSV-1 virus</li>
				<li>Tempomandibular Joint Disorder (TMD)</li>
				<li>Bruxism</li>
				<li>Abnormal bite, irregular and missing teeth occasioning Bruxism</li>
				<li>Sleep Apnia</li>
				<li>Ill-fitting dentures</li>
				<li>Ill-fitting braces</li>
			</ul>
			<p>	
				If you experience regular and chronic headaches, it is important that you seek prompt treatment from TLC Dental. We will review your medical history and will conduct a thorough examination to determine the cause of your headaches.  We will then treat the cause to relieve your headache pain and restore your dental health.<br><br>  
 
				Throughout your examination and treatment you will enjoy the comfort of our signature “Gentle Dentistry.”<br><br>   

